In article <bern.728602443@kleopatra: bern@Uni-Trier.DE (Jochen Bern) writes:
:I once read about a Mechanism which was considered to verify serial Numbers
:painted on nuclear Weapons put under mutual Control: All over the serial
:Number, paint a Layer of a special Color. This Color contains colored Par-
:ticles which will "lump together" when the Paint dries, thus creating a
:random three-dimensional Pattern.

I believe Argonne Lab came up with a clear epoxy mixed with reflective flakes.
They then took a hologram of the thing, which makes it damn near impossible
to duplicate.  Impossible?  I'd never say that.  A variation used fiber optics,
which has some odd quality about being bent.

